Combined with an existing project focused on design feedback to tickets, this backend-architecture project rounds out an “I can own the whole lifecycle” narrative: from spec → architecture → implementation → design review → tickets → releases.

## Extensions and Future Directions

Once a solid MVP exists, several extensions can make the project even more impressive:

- **Import from GitHub**
  - Read an existing codebase and generate a reverse-engineered architecture diagram and PRD.
- **Team Collaboration**
  - Commenting, suggestions, and approvals on proposed architecture diffs.
- **Integration with CI/CD**
  - Generate initial CI pipelines and minimal infra-as-code stubs, aligning with emerging AI-in-infrastructure tools.[5]

These extensions align closely with where generative and agentic AI is heading in software development—automating not just code, but the surrounding architecture and process.[3][1]